metadata.name: Universal Rayhatcher #239
metadata.description:
# What is this?

This is 6942 characters of highly experimental code.

This is a version of my rayhatcher framework (see https://www.fxhash.xyz/article/rayhatching-evolution) that can do literally everything. Or, at least anything you can do within 512 characters of Javascript code. Which is slightly more than a mortal brain can comprehend.

This is my answer to the question: What is the least restrictive set of parameters for fx(params)?

# Should I be minting this?

Depends if you know and like building SDF formulas. Otherwise probably not. Like I said, this is highly experimental code. But it's definitely worth checking the collection and/or secondary for cool stuff that is already minted.

# How does it work?

The minter designs an SDF (Signed Distance Function) which is rendered using my rayhatcher algorithm. They then use the SDF formula in the SDF Code parameter. It's not very complicated, just efficient.

You can press "h" to load the documentation and read about how everything works. Or you can press "d" to read the dev docs. 

# Anything else?

Don't forget that the "Title Seed" param also becomes the "Title" feature of the mint, so make it count.

The params, including the SDF code actually get saved on-chain. Even better, all params and the entire code required to reproduce the image are included in the SVG when saved. See https://twitter.com/piterpasma/status/1649071912742420482 .

metadata.name: Pensado a mano #222
metadata.description:
WARNING: Read instructions so you don’t get a broken token!!
----


Q: Why haven’t you tried fx(params)?
A: Pff.. Sliders?


“Pensado a mano” explores the intersection of Generative Art and Hand Drawing. The collector, by drawing a predefined number of shapes on canvas, creates a unique hand-crafted seed that generates the final artwork. That is the only customisable param, thought by hand, which interacts with various random attributes to produce a unique composition.

“…the time we spend doing and making things, the process…”

And yet the process continues. On the background, the code generates a plottable svg.
An artificially extended process, from hand to screen, from screen to paper, that creates a new kind of mixed media.

Signed plots will soon be claimable via Artfora (tbd price + shipping)


INSTRUCTIONS

1 - Draw the requested shapes and wait to see the result. You can change the Seed Nr. slider if you don't like the selected mode.
2 - Press “C” to copy drawing to Clipboard
3 - Copy the clipboard contents to the text-input on the fx(params) sidebar

***Important. If you buy several tickets, make sure you don't mint the same Seed Nr. twice (slider)

press “S” to save the PNG, press “P” to plot the SVG


DISCLAIMER

This is a high-supply token minted during a bear market. Have Fun.

metadata.name: let me fall #172
metadata.description:
A study of form, empty spaces, panic attacks, asymmetry, tinnitus, chaos, and the never-ending journey to obtain imperfection. 

30 Matisse-inspired palettes.

2-6 – increase resolution.

“f” – add more noise to iteration at current resolution.
“n” – redraw at current resolution without noise.
“s” – save export.

Please be patient while drawing at higher resolutions, it can take quite a while.

Created with p5js.

metadata.name: fx(mash) #39
metadata.description:
fx(mash) is my humble contribution to celebrating #fxhashturnsone

This series is based on a simple algorithm - lines of a random length are drawn on a square grid until the grid is full.

I have added a variety of features based on some of my favorite fxhash projects and a few special guests.

This collection is intentionally diverse and disorderly, that's a nice way of saying I only had a short period of time following the release of Acequia. As a result, some of the outputs might be weird, messy, or even bordering on broken (if you get one of the latter please let me know and I'll reimburse you).

Despite being a bit rough around the edges, I hope fx(mash) reflects some measure of my love for the fxhash community. If you're feeling kind, then perhaps it even harks back to the experimental early days :)

The last year has been an incredible journey, thank you for letting me be a part of our story so far.

Controls (in live view):

- Press [s] to save the current image
- Press [g] to toggle grain
- Press [h] for a high-res output

Beta Controls (in live view, definitely not fully tested):

- Press [p] to start/pause animation
- Press [i] to slow down animation
- Press [o] to speed up animation

All primary sales go to Savepakistan.


Acknowledgements:

fx(mash) uses Gorilla Sun's grain implementation, a big thanks to him and meezwhite for a great article that is well worth supporting https://www.fxhash.xyz/article/all-about-that-grain

metadata.name: Glowing Windows #41
metadata.description:
In each piece, tiny colored dots are placed randomly according to a unique distribution. This creates the illusion of brightly colored windows. The initial distribution may be repeated multiple times in smaller sizes, which shows the motion of going through the window. You are invited to look into the windows and discover what it shows you. Due to the diversity in distributions, amount of colors, colors, and background, every piece is highly unique!

The collection is dedicated to my girlfriend and will open for minting on her birthday. 

Please be patient when exploring the variations, as it takes some time for the millions of dots to be placed.

metadata.name: Interlaced #63
metadata.description:
From African tribal clothes to Islamic mosaics every civilization throughout history has produced delicate patterns to share the essence of their culture. These artifacts have changed our understanding of how art, like societies form through bonds, the very fabric of things that have become symbols for cycles, paths and relationships.

Interlaced explores these unique motifs using emergent algorithms to produce colorful continuous patterns. The project uses a dynamic engine that traverses triangular meshes placing diverse tile configurations. By combining art with technology, the project aims to tell a new story of making digital connections between geography, culture and time.

Press “s” to save in high-resolution.

metadata.name: Dentro #70
metadata.description:
"Dentro" 

Dentro is a captivating art form that captures the multifaceted beauty within each of us. It showcases a diverse range of flowers, from vibrant and vivid to dark and mysterious, mirroring the rich tapestry of our inner souls. These intricate patterns and colors reveal the unique complexities of our emotions, experiences, and perspectives, inviting viewers to explore and embrace the depth of human existence.

It is fully personalized, you can create your own palette to it (just need to check the option for a personalized palette)

made with p5.js, p5.grain and GLSL
Zamboni, March 2023

metadata.name: Velvet #15
metadata.description:
This project explores the interplay of lights, colors, and shapes.
Using p5.js and shaders, I have tried to create a generator that outputs beautiful compositions.
fx(params) gives the collector a lot of control over the final sketch, so take your time and find the params you like.

The default canvas size is 1024 x 1656, but you can render in any size by adding '&scale=' to the URL and specifying a number. 
Press [s] to save as PNG.
